AWARD PURPOSE
THIS IS A COOPERATIVE GRANT AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE DEPARTMENT AND THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF
STATE WORKFORCE AGENCIES (NASWA)/ CENTER FOR EMPLOYMENT SECURITY EDUCATION AND
RESEARCH (CESER). NASWA/CESER IS THE ONLY QUALIFIED ENTITY TO DO THIS WORK.
NASWA/CESER IS THE ONLY QUALIFIED ENTITY TO DO THIS WORK. THEY HAVE THE ORGANIZATIONAL
CAPACITY AND EXPERTISE (SUBJECT MATTER AND TECHNICAL) TO ENSURE THAT ICON MAINTAINS OPERATIONS
THROUGH THE EXISTING CONTRACTOR WITH NO BREAK IN SERVICE AND TO IMMEDIATELY ENGAGE IN PREPARING
FOR MODERNIZATION OF ICON AND MANAGING THE NEXT PROCUREMENT CYCLE. NASW A/CESER HAS A
UNIQUE RELATIONSHIP TO STATE UI AGENCIES AND ALREADY PLAYS KEY ROLES IN ICON OPERATIONS THAT
POSITION THEM TO TAKE ON THE NEW FUNCTIONS OF MANAGING ICON OVERALL.

ACTIVITIES PERFORMED
ICON SUPPORTS AN ENVIRONMENT COMPRISED OF SEVERAL MAINFRAMES, PERSONAL COMPUTERS, WORKSTATIONS,
OPERATING SYSTEMS AND TELECOMMUNICATION METHODOLOGIES. EACH OF THE FIFTY-THREE STATES ACCESSES THE
NETWORK VIA DIFFERENT COMMUNICATION PROTOCOLS.
CURRENT ICON APPLICATIONS SUPPORTING UNEMPLOYMENT INSURANCE (UI) ACTIVITIES INCLUDE:
1) INTERSTATE BENEFITS (IB) CLAIMS DATA EXCHANGE;
2) INTERSTATE STATISTICAL EXCHANGE;
3) INTERSTATE WAGE DATA EXCHANGE;
4) DATA EXCHANGE BETWEEN SWAS AND SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA);
5) INTERSTATE CROSS-MATCH ANDLOCATOR;
6) UI FEDERAL REPORTING;
7) UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION FOR FEDERAL EMPLOYEES (UCFE)WAGE TRANSFER;
8) UCFE/ UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION FOR EX-SERVICE MEMBERS (UCX) QUERY VERIFICATION;
9) FEDERAL CLAIMS CONTROL CENTER (FCCC);
10) FCCC EXCEPTIONS;
11) UI MAIL;
12) LIABLE/DATA AGENT TRANSFER (LADT);
13) AUTOMATED CLAIMS HANDBOOK;
14) VESSELS HANDBOOK;
15) STATE UNEMPLOYMENT TAX ACT (SUTA) DUMPING INFORMATION COLLABORATION (SDIC)
SYSTEM;
16) COMBINE WAGE CLAIMS (CWC 02-12);
17) MILITARY STATE DATA EXCHANGE SYSTEM (MSDES); AND
18) FEDERAL EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION ACT (FECA) CROSSMATCH.
DELIVERABLES/

DELIVERABLES
THE NASWA UI
COMMITTEE AND INTERSTATE BENEFITS SUBCOMMITTEE FUNCTION AS A "USERS GROUP" FOR ICON AND
HELP STEER ICON FUNCTIONALITY. IN ADDITION NASWA MANAGES THE MEMORANDA OF UNDERSTANDING
AMONG THE STATES THAT ENABLES THE INFORMATION SHARING ACROSS STATES. NASWA/CESER ALSO
OPERATES THE UI INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY SUPPORT CENTER (ITSC) WHICH IS ALREADY PLAYING A KEY
ROLE IN SHAPING THE BUSINESS REQUIREMENTS AND ARCHITECTURE OF A MODERNIZED ICON SYSTEM IN
PARTNERSHIP WITH ETA.

INTENDED BENEFICIARY
NASWA/CESER HAS A STRONG RELATIONSHIP WITH ETA AS A RESULT OF MANAGING MULTIPLE UI
ENTITIES AS DISCUSSED ABOVE AND THE ABILITY TO LEVERAGE THESE INVESTMENTS IN WAYS THAT WILL
PROMOTE EFFICIENCIES AND SAVE MONEY

